# Enterprise IAM Onboarding Lab

## Overview
This project simulates onboarding a business application into an Identity Governance and Administration (IGA) environment. The lab demonstrates identity lifecycle management, role-based access control (RBAC), entitlement mapping, and access validation processes aligned with enterprise IAM practices.

## Objectives
- Simulate application onboarding into IAM controls
- Implement RBAC using Active Directory groups
- Demonstrate identity lifecycle workflows
- Document onboarding evidence and validation steps


## Technologies Used
- Windows Server (Active Directory)
- Azure AD / Entra ID
- VirtualBox
- PowerShell
- Microsoft Excel (Access Reviews)

![image alt](https://github.com/9gfp56zb48-ui/My-Portfolio/blob/e8ec26542bbcb845d2adb55c37eedc338c9721ac/images/LABArchitecture.png)

## IAM Concepts Demonstrated
- Identity Governance (IGA)
- Access Provisioning
- Entitlement Management
- Access Reviews
- Least Privilege
- Audit Evidence Collection

## Lab Workflow
1. Create users and departments
2. Define entitlements (security groups)
3. Assign role-based access
4. Perform access validation
5. Document onboarding evidence

## Validation Steps
- Verified user authentication
- Confirmed group membership inheritance
- Tested privileged access restrictions

## Key Takeaways
This lab demonstrates how enterprise IAM teams onboard applications while maintaining governance, compliance, and secure access controls.
